<subSubSection id="C30A6528FFB7FF85C5BC1883FD5BF9B0" pageId="21" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAF36A3FFB7FF85C5BC1883FD5BF9B0" blockId="21.[174,1126,1260,1589]" pageId="21" pageNumber="56">
Taxonomic notes.This species shows nearly the same colour variations as 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB7FF85C5861960FED1FAAD" baseAuthorityName="Hufnagel" baseAuthorityYear="1766" box="[208,339,1294,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosa">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB7FF85C5861960FED1FAAD" box="[208,339,1294,1320]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="56">P. nebulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it was considered by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B52FFB7FF85C7CC1961FC01FAAD" author="HEYDEMANN, F." box="[666,899,1294,1320]" pageId="21" pageNumber="56" pagination="12 - 33" refId="ref10990" refString="HEYDEMANN, F. (1944): Zur Kenntnis der Gattung Aplecta Guen. und zweiter &quot; Dual Species &quot; inderselben (Lep. Noct.). - Entomologische Zeitung des Entomologischen Vereins zu Stettin 105: 12 - 33." type="journal article" year="1944">HEYDEMANN (1944)</bibRefCitation>
as subspecies this species despite of the expressed differences in genitalia of both sexes and the reduction of the male brush organ. The most remarkable trend is in this species the rudimentation of the distal section of the left saccular process connected with the reduction of the distal bundle of bristles which also has some geographical variation. The species is widely distributed in the boreal and nemoral forest zones of North America and shows only some clinal variation with the exception of the Vancouver Island population (
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB7FF85C6091995FE61F9B0" authority="Barnes &amp; Benjamin, 1924" authorityName="Barnes &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="1924" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Aplecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nimbosa" subSpecies="mysticoides">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB7FF85C6091995FBE4F996" box="[863,1126,1529,1555]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="56">P. nimbosa mysticoides</emphasis>
Barnes &amp; Benjamin, 1924
</taxonomicName>
; see: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B52FFB7FF85C7751A74FD4FF9B0" author="MCCABE, T. M." box="[547,717,1563,1589]" pageId="21" pageNumber="56" pagination="1 - 141" refId="ref11622" refString="MCCABE, T. M. (1980): A reclassification of the Polia complex for North America (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae). - New York State Museum, Bulletin No. 432. i - vi, 1 - 141 pp." type="book chapter" year="1980">MCCABE 1980</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
